title: Fantastic set of brushes in a nice case!
text:
[[VIDEOID:f0c2bad6411cb1763775ff07a47ae6b]] [[VIDEOID:b28c8169ff4b8186d0a5677e1564a732]] [[VIDEOID:868d17a43bf44324e45b16ef2516f38f]] I own a lot of makeup brushes, its a bit of an obsession of mine and Ive become pretty picky when it comes to quality of brushes. There are a few things I look to determine the quality of brushes and theyre how well the brushes are put together, how soft the bristles are, and if the bristles are thick and full. This brush set meets all of my requirements so Im pretty pleased with this set.

This is a set of 32 brushes, with most of the brushes being eye shadow brushes. These come in a nice roll up case that has a kind of pleather look and feel to it. When you have the case rolled up it takes up very little room considering there are 32 brushes in it, which is great for traveling.

The metal piece that connects the handles to the bristles is called a ferrule. Ive gotten some lower quality sets where these are poorly glued together and are loose when they arrive and easily come apart. These came glued together very well and held up when washed. The bristles are super soft and they are nice and thick too. When you pull on the bristles you dont get a ton of fall out either, so this is another sign of good quality. You may notice a bit of a smell when you open them but washing them thoroughly will get rid of that smell and its not uncommon for brushes to smell like that when brand new. I really like the variety of brushes and this is a great set at an affordable price.

title: Definitely firms and moisturizes. Loving the green tea ingredient!
text:
I've tried out a few different firming serums lately, in the quest to keep my skin moisturized and looking its best. I was drawn to Derma-Nu after reading numerous good reviews, as well as wanting to try a serum with green tea in the ingredients. Most of the other serums I have purchased do not have green tea as a listed ingredient, and I'm really a big fan of all of the benefits of it, so I was sold!

The bottle of serum comes with a pamphlet showing other products by Derma-Nu that are suggested as being used in conjunction with this firming serum, as well as a pamphlet showing their line of products for complete body skin care. Anyway, let's get back to this serum! I'm a fan of hyaluronic acid and it's ability to hold 1000 times its weight in water. In this serum, the mixture has been infused with vitamin C, vitamin E, and green tea for their anti-aging properties. The serum itself is very fluid, and it takes about a nickel sized amount to cover my whole face and neck area. It spreads evenly and smoothly, and takes a moment to absorb, so it's easy to make sure you've covered all of the important areas (some other serums I've purchased tend to absorb so quickly that I can't get it distributed evenly). I would recommend using a moisturizer after letting the serum soak in for a few minutes. My skin feels fantastic after using this, and I've noticed the skin under my eyes feeling firmer just after using this a few times.

title: Works wonders for taming frizz. Smells like clove though, not citrus.
text:
Ladies and gentlemen, let me appeal to the ladies on the great results that beard oil can have on your hair. If you have wavy, frizzy, unmanageable hair (as I do), this could really help! I had been using argan oil and other oil blends to tame my wild hair, and when I read the ingredients in my roommate's beard oil and saw how similar they were, I wanted to give it a try. I first bought the Tea Tree blend by Beardsmen Spirit, since I'm a big fan of the benefits of tea tree oil, and I liked it so much that I wanted to try out this Rousing Citrus blend.

As far as ingredients go, the Rousing Citrus blend has Jojoba seed oil, sweet almond oil, grape seed oil, glycerin, grapefruit peel oil, lemon fruit oil, blood orange essential oil, clove flower oil, and vanilla plantifolia fruit essential oil. I compared this to the ingredients in the Tea Tree blend, which are Jojoba seed oil, sweet almond oil, grape seed oil, glycerin, peppermint essential oil, tea tree leaf essential oil, and vanilla plantifolia fruit essential oil. Not too big of a difference except for the obvious different essential oils. This oil has about the same thick consistency, and a little bit goes a long way! It takes about 5-6 drops of the oil to tame the frizz in my hair that's about 4 inches down past my shoulders.

One con for me though: this oil does not really have a citrus smell. I smell clove over everything else, and while this isn't a bad thing, I was really hoping for those lemon and blood orange essential oils to be prominent. So a more appropriate name for this would be "Rousing Clove".

title: Love For Women, 1.9 Fl. Oz
text:
[[ASIN:B01ETYVW3G Love For Women, 1.9 Fl. Oz. / 55 ml - Inspired By Onika By Nicki Minaj Perfume]]

I really enjoy trying different parfums to help me find a new fresh scent or to combine with other scents to come up with my own combined signature scent. The seller does a wonderful job of delivering quickly and well packaged. The cologne is very pretty in it's design in a feminine curved bottle with black lace on the front which looks nice on my dresser or vanity.This perfume definitely smells great. It has a sheer musk undertone that is very inviting, you can also smell fruitiness and a slight hint floral and sweet undertones like flowers. It is a very feminine scent but also very seductive but not overpowering. It's difficult to describe scents but all I can say is it really does smell wonderful, it doesn't give me a headache and my fiance loves it. I find that it lasts longer if I spay it on pulse points. I receive complements a lot of times while wearing it I definitely recommend this wonderful perfume and would absolutely say try it. This is a 1.9 ounce bottle at under 13.00 delivered to your door. I purchased this product at a discounted price in exchange for my honest review. The discount I received will not alter my honest opinion in any way. Since I count on honest product reviews to make my selections on Amazon, I will always be forthcoming and sincere in all my reviews. No matter if the product is discounted or not, I will leave honest feedback that I base on my own personal experience with the product I receive. *One last note, I wasn't sure what the difference in Eau De Parfum and Perfume is, so I looked it up. Here's what I found on the web on perfume website:
Eau de parfum. "After the top notes have died away, the middle notes or heart notes of a perfume become noticeable. This is the focus of eau de parfum which makes it perfect to spray on hair or clothing. (Be careful with delicate fabrics such as silk, though, as they may stain.) The concentration of oils is over 15%, sometimes reaching as high as 20%. Since it is less intense than perfume extract, it is also cheaper, but it usually lasts well and is sold in small sizes." So it is stronger than Eau de Cologne which contains about 7% essence dissolved in alcohol of 60 or 70, and stronger than Eau de toilette which contains around 10% aromatic essence. But not as strong as Perfume. This is the strongest of scents because of the higher concentration of essences as much as 40% by volume.

title: # Single For Men, Eau De Toilette 3.3 Fl. Oz.
text:
[[ASIN:B01ETWZRL6 # Single For Men, Eau De Toilette 3.3 Fl. Oz./ 100 ml - Inspired By The One Cologne]]

I was looking for new scents or signature scents for my future husband and wanted to try this. I like and appreciate the scent of The One Colognes so this was one I wanted my fiance (Bobby) try this scent. Buying signature scents can become quite expensive to say the least and this is a way for us to get an idea of what a scent smells like with Bobby's chemistry without spending thirty five or forty dollars and then not like it. Besides if this cologne scent stays on and lasts a while we may opt to purchase the less expensive cologne. The seller delivered very quickly and we received packaged well. Since this cologne is an Eau De Toilette Spray, it will have slightly more of the oils (10%) that make the spray smell great than just cologne which has about 7% oil. The scent also is delivered in a convenient spray which me and Bobby both like. The cologne actually smells very nice on him. It's a sort of woodsy, citrus masculine scent and you can definitely smell oranges and ginger in it. The One Cologne describes the scent as "Coriander, Grapefruit, Cardamom seed, Tobacco, Basil, Cedar, Ambre, Ginger, Orange Blossom." Some of those things I have no idea what they smell like, but I'd say this not really a musk based scent but it smells really yummy on Bobby. It takes a little more spray than the original version The One Cologne, however, it's about 1/3 the cost, so I won't complain. It's still pretty strong with a couple of sprays being all he needs. As far as wear, it lasts a long time. It's sensual/manly in it's scent and he said he received several complements on the cologne. It is also a large bottle at 3.3 ounces delivered to the door for under 15.00. We like the cologne and can recommend it.

title: Works well, but detailed instructions would have been helpful...
text:
For me, this little nail drill works very well. It's touted as being good for beginners, but I was really nervous about using it for the first time, because it came with absolutely no instructions. Yikes! I'd cut my nails down to nubbins, and have been wearing falsies, so I figured it was a great way to get some practice.

There are a few notes on the product listing about how to insert and remove the drill bits, so with that being all I had to go on, I just went for it.

As I had no clue as to which bits were for what job, I had to wing it. I tried two. The first I tried wasn't quite coarse enough, so I went with the larger, barrel-shaped bit, which worked well for what I wanted. I'd basically put on some stiletto tips, and managed to jab every family member at least once. I didn't want to completely remove them, but I wanted to take them down a bit and round out the tips. Once I changed the bit this drill did a great job.

It got a little warm, but didn't get too hot, and it didn't overheat and stop on me. In my photo is what they looked like right after I was done. I did go over the edges briefly with an emery board for the couple of rough spots left, simply because I'm not yet quite adept enough to get the perfect shaping I want, but practice is key.

It's for the same reason that I haven't yet tried the drill on my natural nails. I will, though, once I get a little more know-how under my belt. So, in summary, I like it, and it seems to be beginner-friendly, but I wish there were detailed information available on its use.

I received this nail drill free to try in exchange for my evaluation and unbiased review. Any opinion I've expressed is purely mine and based on my own personal experience using this drill.

title: Anti Aging Serum - The Best Hyaluronic Acid Face Cream Moisturizer
text:
[[ASIN:B01699WMHO Anti Aging Serum - The Best Hyaluronic Acid Face Cream Moisturizer for Anti Wrinkle & Skin Tightening Night Cream. Tempt by Cazbe Skin Care Products Rejuvenate your youthful glow]]

I am always looking for something that will help me turn back the hands of time. I want to look good for as long as I can and because of that I've often used Vitamin C serums. I know they are effective and help with aging skin a lot, My skin has always been a challenge. I have oily skin with large pores and sometimes have uneven and dull skin. I also have some expression lines on my forehead. I wanted to start using this serum as soon as I got it home. The serum comes in a very nice bottle which I like a lot because not only is it pretty but the serum is delivered in an airless pump which distributes exactly the right amount of serum to my fingertips for easy application to my face. Since Vitamin C products are easily oxidized I appreciate the product being dispensed this way so that it protects the serum and keeps it effective. I have been using this serum the morning on cleansed skin after toner, and then again at night before moisturizer on clean skin in the same way. The serum has a nice scent that is not overpowering and it only takes a pump or two of the serum to cover my entire face. The serum doesn't feel greasy or oily and it's just the right consistency to spread easily. There was no burning or irritation with this product, and it absorbs well into my skin with no left over residue. My skin feels smooth, silky and refreshed after I apply this serum as if my face has a refreshing blast of moisture. It looks supple and moisturized for hours and I've noticed my makeup stays on better. I have been using the serum for about two weeks now. Since then I have noticed a lot of amount of improvement in the tone and smoothness of my skin. It doesn't look as dull and my skin also looks firmer. My skin is more radiant and soft and the expression lines in my forehead appear a little softer and the improved clarity of my skin is noticeable. My skin also looks better when I'm not wearing makeup. My skin has improved a little and I've been asked what had I been doing to make my skin look better? That makes me feel more confident that the serum is working. I am going to continue to use this serum and consider it a good value worth every penny of the asking price here since a little goes a long way.

title: Great product and great results
text:
Searching for a safe and effective skin brightener is always my top priority because I have a never ending battle with skin discoloration and dark sunspots. I love the fact that this serum is gentle and does not contain the harsh chemicals that most skin lighteners do because I prefer using products that have natural and botanical ingredients as much as possible. This product comes in a dark amber dropper bottle which protects the product from sunlight exposure. It also contains Glycolic and Kojic Acids as the key ingredients which I believe will lead to clear and brighter looking skin. This serum keeps my skin smooth, shining and flake-free. It is not greasy and does not form a film. I have somewhat sensitive skin which is pone to irritation and redness, but this serum is very gentle without causing any breakouts or negative side effects. I believe it has been gradually improving my dull looking appearance by making the spots a bit lighter.

I use the product as directed after cleansing, toning my face and allowing some time to dry before topping with my regular moisturizer. This light weight clear serum not only applies smoothly and evenly, but it also has a fresh light scent that will dissipate after it dries. It has a liquid gel like texture which leaves my skin soft and smooth, not to mention it is also fast absorbing without any uncomfortable feeling and leaves my face quite moisturized. I have even started using it to lighten the sun spots on my hands and the results are impressive. Although I have not been using it for long, my skin tone has started to look more even and I have also noticed that some of my blemishes have cleared up along the way. My darker spots still exist, but they look much better and I can see some significant improvements of my lighter ones.

I am sure everyone's skin is different, but I have experienced zero sensitivity or dryness. I love how much clearer my skin looks throughout the day and my skin feels more balanced. My overall appearance is much brighter and smoother. The brown spots on my hands are slowly fading in under two weeks and I can say that I am really happy about it. In fact, everybody's skin type is different and the effects may not be the same or visible for everyone. I have used it twice a day for quite some time now and the brightening effect seems to be progressing. There is no miraculous or overnight whitening as such, but with gradual fading of sun spots, my face does appear clearer and even toned. This product does what it promises and lightens my dark spots. This is a great and reasonably priced dark spot corrector serum that I will definitely buy again and I feel quite confident to explore other products from the same line to further improve my skin conditions.

Disclosure: I purchased this dark spot corrector at a discount for my honest and unbiased review.

title: This stuff is AMAZING!!! You can see results in a matter of days! If you have cellulite, you have to try this cream!
text:
I try my best to stay as fit as I possibly can, but there are those problem areas that seem to haunt you no matter what you do. For me, that area is the back of my upper thighs. While this area is not bad, there are small areas where the cellulite is noticeable. As soon as this cream arrived I started using it twice a day, once in the morning and then again before bedtime. The instructions also ask that you apply the cream in a circular motion. This was a bit more difficult since I was rubbing the back of my own thighs, but I eventually got into a rhythm and was able to get a circular motion going on. Since this item arrived in the afternoon, I was only able to apply this cream once the first day. Did not notice too much of a difference the following morning, but I was not going to give up that fast. Applied it again after my shower and went about my day. That evening when I went to look at my thighs, for some reason one of them looked better than the other one. Much smoother and tighter!! I thought maybe I had spent more time on that thigh than I did with the other one, so this time I focused more on the thigh that looked the worst. Woke up the following morning and both of my thighs looked amazing!!! The skin looked tighter and there were fewer dimples. I have been applying this cream every day as instructed and I cannot even tell that I had cellulite just the week before. This stuff is AMAZING!!

This product contains an intelligent dual active formula. This formula contains Adiposlim 3%, a cellulite fat burning compound that drastically minimizes fat in different parts of the body. It actually shrinks fat cells below the skin to help rid the skin of that spongy layer of fat that usually forms over muscles. Adiposlim 3% also collects fat cells which are burned off for energy during physical activity and restricts the combination of free fatty acids that collect in adipocytes to dramatically minimize parts of the body with fat deposits. Adipoless 1% helps in preventing new fat from forming. This fat-fighting compound works by maintaining fat loss results, and it avoids the growth of new adipocytes and the combination that keeps fat cells in their dormant state so they remain in their shrunken state. Adipoless 1% also provides anti-adipogenesis action restricting the formation and maturation of new fat cells that can lead to fat deposits over time. That may sound like a bunch of jibberish to some, but to sum it up, it means this cream will not only get rid of the cellulite, but it will also keep it from coming back! It does not get better than that. I love this cream! Best I have ever tried, and I have tried many!

My experience with other cellulite remover creams have been decent, but this cream works miracles! Now I want to work on other parts of my body, although I may not have enough cellulite to see any results. I am very pleased with this cream! Will continue to use it until I am not able to get anything else out of the bottle!! Then I can order more!! Buyers note: I did receive this cellulite remover cream at a discounted rate in exchange for my honest and unbiased review, but that has no bearing on my review. This is the real deal of cellulite creams. Please vote if this review was helpful in any way. Thanks in advance!

Even though it feels light on the skin, it helps my makeup glide on smoothly with absolute moisture. It feels like it disappears as soon as it is rubbed in, and yet it keeps my skin perfectly balanced and moisturized all day without the shiny greasy looking. I especially need something to help my sensitive skin stay hydrated and soft. This moisturizer seems to have just the right formula for that purpose without causing any breakouts.

This facial moisturizer is rich and creamy. I really appreciate that this product is not greasy or sticky. When using this moisturizer, I can actually feel it sink into my skin pretty fast. It instantly makes my face feel very smooth and it soaks in rather quickly without leaving any uncomfortable residues. I have been using this cream twice a day and always making sure to cover my eyelids as well. It is so gentle for my sensitive skin that my skin does not itch or turn red. It is not greasy, but the coverage is thick enough to sufficiently provide moisture for night time. I do not like oily or sticky moisturizers, but I do prefer certain degree of a good moisturizing coverage. This is a very good face cream compared to many other brands of moisturizers that I have used not to mention the fact that it is made by skin healthy ingredients and botanical extracts.

title: Vague Label Ingredients, But Lathers Well, Smells Good
text:
I am pretty picky when it comes to my body washes. I like one that has good ingredients, and a great smell. When I saw the label for this saying Argan Oil, Coconut Oil and Tea Tree Oil, I knew it would be right up my alley. I love all 3 of those ingredients and they work well with my skin. I was excited to use this. When it arrived and I checked the ingredients label, I was shocked. Like so many other reviews, I don't see any of the above listed on the label. Some ingredients are very vague. Some of the ingredients I had never heard of before and had to look up. My suggestion to the company is to make the label a bit more descriptive and clearly put what is inside. What essences? What type of vegetable oils? Since it is so unclear, if you have easily irritated or sensitive skin I would stay away from this. The vague label makes it hard to use by anyone who may have allergies to certain things.

On the other hand, I will say that I do like the body wash. It smells fantastic, like a herbal scent. It lathers nicely and feels good on the skin. Doesn't dry my skin out.

If the label was changed and I knew exactly what was in this I would easily bump this up to a 5 star rating. But because I have no clue what is inside this, I have to bump it down.

*Please note that I was sent this product either complimentary or discounted in order to provide my honest experience, thoughts and review.

title: light and awesome
text:
why use a primer... well below are some reasons why you must:)

I loved this one because you need very little to make your face looks all smooth and fresh.

read what else I found:
If you havent been using makeup primer, then youre really missing out.

Whether you wear a full face of makeup everyday or you prefer to keep it simple with BB cream and tinted lip balm, makeup primer is a godsend when trying to combat shine or create a smooth base for foundation.

Yet, many people often skip this step because they believe they dont really need it, are unsure of how to use it or dont think its worth the investment. However, using primer underneath your makeup will make everything last longer, whether thats on your skin or in your cosmetics bag. We asked two beauty experts to discuss the ins and outs of primer and why its a must-have. Heres the deal.

Makeup primer is a base for foundation or face makeup that allows it to go on smoother and last longer.

Formulas are available in cream, gel and powder. While moisturizer softens skin, editorial and celebrity makeup artist Stephen Dimmick points out that primer prepares skin for your favorite tinted moisturizer or foundation, giving it something to hold onto so it lasts throughout the day.

Many makeup primers are formulated with silicone-based polymers like dimethicone because of their ultra-smoothing effects. But for those who struggle with cystic acne and other skin conditions, do a patch test or check with a medical professional before use, as there have been reports of allergic reactions to dimethicone.

Physicians Formulas celebrity makeup artist Joanna Schlip adds that makeup primers can also help smooth any fine lines, wrinkles or large pores. If you are searching for a face primer to help color-correct rosacea or conceal acne spots, Schlips go-to is this light green primer as that hue cancels out redness.

Primers are even available just for your eyelids to prevent creasing. Id recommend pairing a primer with extra long-wear [eyeshadow or eyeliner] formulas for a look that will really stay put, says Schlip. If you have oilier eylids, Dimmick advises that you use a mattifying eyelid primer.

Using your fingertips to apply makeup primer allows you to really work the product into your skin.

Schlip thinks its best to apply primer with fingertips for areas larger than a quarter. If only using for small areas, Id recommend a brush. I like to use a concealer or lip brush for this, she said. This spot-treat technique gives the look of a more natural finish, according to Schlip.

Taking this routine a step further, Dimmick considers the process an exercise for the face. He explains that massaging primer onto skin with fingertips helps to get the blood flowing underneath. Well consider that the next time were meditating while putting on makeup.

Primer is a life-saver for getting your makeup to stay-put in extreme weather.

If you live, visit or plan on traveling anywhere that experiences hot and humid or cold and dry temperatures, Schlip suggests having primer handy to help your makeup wear longer. However, Dimmick advocates for using primer year-round. No matter what the weather is like outside, this extra step will save you a lot of time and effort.

Primer can even be worn on its own.
Love the fresh no-makeup look but want to look a bit more polished than when you first woke up? Primer is your answer. The product can be worn on your eyelids and double as a light eyeshadow, or it can serve as a lighter alternative to foundation.

title: my friend bought this and recommended it. I must say I love it
text:
my friend bought this and recommended it. I must say I love it. Hyaluronic works because :
I have a new skincare obsession: hyaluronic acid. Ive been using hyaluronic acid for about a month and Im amazed at what its done for my acne-prone skin. Inspired to learn more about how the stuff works (and if its really ok to put something involving the word acid on your face), I talked to a few experts to find out what hyaluronic acid is and why, exactly, its so awesome.

I first read about this magical stuff called hyaluronic acid over on I Heart Daily (tons of good stuff over there, all the time, by the way!). Then I found it recommended over and over again as an ingredient in facial creams in the beauty magazines I read on a recent flight. So I thought, why not try it? I ordered up a bottle and started using it, twice a day.

And whoa. When I layer this on underneath my regular daily moisturizer with SPF, my skin looks incredibly dewy. Yup, dewy. Id always read that word in beauty mags but thought it was just an overused editorial clich, not a descriptor that could ever be applied to my own skin, with its large pores and tendency towards oiliness. But dewy it was. And the acne thats plagued me since 7th grade (over half of my life) has considerably lessened, too. All of a sudden, I have beautiful, clear, perfectly moisturized skin, even in the dead of winter.

Im pretty committed to being as natural as possible with my skincare, meaning I try to buy products that use ingredients sourced from nature rather than chemicals and plasticizers. I knew I loved hyaluronic acid, but I wanted to know more about what it actually was and if it fell into my own admittedly loose category of natural. (Yes, I know I probably should have done more research before I started slathering it all over my face.) Heres what I found out:
What Is Hyaluronic Acid?

Hyaluronic acid isnt necessarily a new ingredient in skincare, but its been growing in popularity in recent years. According to Dr. Jessica Krant, dermatologist, founder of Art of Dermatology and Assistant Clinical Professor of Dermatology at SUNY Downstate Medical Center:

Hyaluronic acid, or hyaluronan, is the bodys lubricant molecule. It is basically a very big and complex sugar-related molecule called a glycosaminoglycan that is found naturally throughout the body and works in many different ways to keep us healthy and active. Its involved in the health and function of skin, joints, and the immune system, among others. It is very popular as used in a number of cosmetic fillers known as hyaluronic acid dermal fillers, which get injected under the surface of the skin to replace lost volume and fill deep folds. Lately, topical products have begun to include the molecule as a moisturizing or antiaging ingredient.

So, its found naturally in the body and is commonly used in fillers. Ok. But if its found in the body, where, exactly, does the hyaluronic acid that I use on my face come from? Cosmetic dermatologist Dr. Oscar Hevia explained that cosmetic hyaluronic acid is made in a lab:

The current method of production involves bacterial fermentation, a process whereby genetically modified bacteria can produce the hyaluronic acid in large quantities which is then filtered extensively to obtain a purified, finished product.

Is Hyaluronic Acid Natural?

So is something thats made in a lab natural? Dr. Hevia continued:

it depends how you define natural. Most would probably not utilize this term for a substance that is produced by genetically modified bacteria, but nonetheless, the finished product is pure and identical to human hyaluronic acid.

read this article to make an informed decision:
What Is Skin Bleaching?

Skin bleaching is a cosmetic treatment to reduce the prominence of skin discolorations and even out the color of the skin. You can buy bleaching creams over the counter and by prescription.

Some people apply skin lightener to their entire body to change their complexion, but this can be very risky. The active ingredient in some skin lighteners is mercury, so bleaching can lead to mercury poisoning.

Mercury is a toxic agent that can cause serious psychiatric, neurological, and kidney problems. Pregnant women who use a skin lightener with mercury can pass the mercury to their unborn child.

The use of mercury as an ingredient in skin lighteners is banned in the U.S. However, some skin lighteners produced outside the U.S. may still contain mercury.
How Do Skin Lighteners Work?

Skin lighteners contain an active ingredient or a combination of ingredients that reduces the amount of melanin in the skin where it is applied.

How Do Skin Lighteners Work? continued...

The most widely used ingredient in skin lighteners sold in the U.S. is hydroquinone.

The FDA regulates the use of hydroquinone in the U.S. Over-the-counter skin lighteners can contain up to 2% hydroquinone. Dermatologists can write prescriptions for lighteners that contain 4%-6% hydroquinone.

It's important to check with your doctor before using a product with hydroquinone and to follow the doctor's directions exactly.

Other skin lighteners use drugs such as steroids and retinoic acid, which comes from vitamin A, as active ingredients. And some skin lighteners use natural ingredients such as kojic acid -- a compound that comes from a fungus -- and arbutin, a compound found in various plants.
Risks of Skin Lighteners

One of the most significant risks of using some skin lighteners is the potential exposure to mercury. One study found that nearly 1 out of every 4 skin lighteners made in Asia and sold outside the U.S. contained mercury.

There are other potential risks of skin lighteners. Those risks can include the following:

Prolonged use can contribute to premature aging of skin.
Long-term use may increase the risk of skin cancer from sun exposure. Always use sunscreen when using a skin lightener and going out in the sun.
Steroids in some skin lighteners may increase risk for skin infections, skin thinning, acne, and poor wound healing.
Applying steroids to large areas of skin may put you at risk for health problems related to steroid being absorbed by the body.
Hydroquinone may cause unwanted and untreatable skin discoloration (ochronosis).
Various bleaching agents, including natural ingredients, can cause skin irritation or allergic reaction.

title: It actually works!  This is pretty amazing on my curly hair!
text:
I am always sceptical when I see advertisements on TV for products that seem 'AMAAAAZZZZING! MUST BUY NOW!!'
I wasn't too sure what to expect with this. I thought it was gimmicky, but I am happy to be proven wrong.
This is so much easier to use than a flat iron.
I like that it has a digital LCD that shows you what temperature the brush is heating up to. It gives the heat range that your hair styling should be at depending on thickness, etc. I set mine to 230, the hottest setting and it worked great for my thick, curly hair.
It heats up very quickly and the hand grip is comfortable. The cord rotates from the end and the grip on the back of the wand feels nice in the hand.
The rubbery nubs on the ends of the bristles offer some flexibility, but they are not as flexible as your hairbrush. They are also shorter, too.
The way that you do this is to start with clean, well brushed hair. As the bristles are short, they will not detangle for you. Have your hair prepped and ready. If you use a smoothing serum, it would be perfect to add it before you start with this.
You simply brush it over your hair like you would a hairbrush. You can brush from underneath or on top to make sure that all the hair gets close to the heated plate of the brush.
You can spend more time on areas that you want straightened more but I found that my doing my hair in pieces (held up with an alligator clip) worked best for me.
In order to get to the roots at the scalp, it was very easy. The brush is easy to angle towards the scalp and it gets about 1/2" away from the scalp easily and starts straightening from there.
If you hair is damp, you will see some steam, but you'd expect that with a curling iron or flatiron, too.
This actually worked so well, my kids wanted to try it out and they loved it!
The only concern that I had was that if you hair is the type to come out when you brush it, it will come out when you use this, too. The issue was removing the hair from the straightener. It is HOT. I had to work quickly to sweep the excess hair from the brush to toss. I will keep a wide tooth comb by this the next time I use it so I can run it over the bristles and remove the hair.
All in all: I give this a strong thumbs up!
I can't speak about the others on the market, but this one really does what it says it will do. It is way better than a flat iron. It covers more ground and feels more comfortable in the hand. Its a natural movement to brush your hair and this is no different.
Excellent new beauty tool! Very happy that this does what it claims to do! Part of my daily hair regime now!

title: Too good
text:
It is often claimed that periorbital dark circles are caused by tiredness or working too hard or even just staying up late. While this can be true, the truth is that your genes play a huge role here. So what exactly is happening when you get dark circles under or around your eyes?

Simply put, periorbital dark circles are a result of the thin layer of skin below your eyes showing the blood vessels and the blood they contain more clearly than anywhere else on your body. (For reference, this skin around your eyelids, called periorbital skin, is on average about 0.5 mm thick compared to an average of about 2 mm thick on most of the rest of your body.)

Now, as you may or may not already know, the reason veins often look blue isnt because the blood inside them is blue; its because your skin/subcutaneous tissue only lets blue/violet wavelengths of light pass through it. As a result, only blue light is reflected back and the veins look, well, bluish. (Veins often wont appear blue if a person has darker or lighter skin. Rather, the veins tend to appear green or brown. On the other hand, people with extremely light skin, such as albinos, will typically have veins that show up as dark purple or dark red, more closely resembling the actual color of the blood running through the veins.)

Its the exact same concept with the skin below your eyes. Those dark bluish circles are (usually) just the result of light being reflected back off of the blood vessels sitting just below the surface of that incredibly thin patch of skin. This is the same reason facial bruises are more prominent below or around the eyes; the thin skin just shows the blood from the ruptured blood vessels a little bit more clearly.

Again, as you may or may not know, as we age, our skin loses its elasticity and ability to regenerate and as a result, it becomes thinner. This is why more often than not, elderly people will have rather prominent periorbital dark circles regardless of how much they sleep. As with those who are genetically predisposed to having thinner skin below the eyes, its just biology.

title: IF your blowdryer is a match for this diffuser, you are going to want it for lift and volume. Nothing else compares.
text:
Several years ago I had purchased a blowdryer with a similar attachment. I absolutely adored that thing - you could use it on the top of your hair or the sides to give lift so your hair had volume without using any product or doing any backbrushing. The thing was a miracle worker!

Then we entered the era of pin straight hair, and volume and body were out. Thank God, we seem to be passing that era, but hairstyling implements seem to be lagging behind. I was dying to try this diffuser to see if it emulated the gizmo from long ago, and it does. Well made hair styling tool that gives lift and volume to your hair, I love it. Well, kinda.

I'm not sure how 'universal' this is. I tried it on my current blowdryer, and it didn't fit. I had to go digging around until I finally found a Conair dryer upon which it fit, and the funny thing is that it fit like it was MADE for the dryer. The odd thing is that the Conair looks to have the same kind of nozzle the other blowdryer had, so go figger.

IF you have a blowdryer that marries this diffuser well, this is definitely something you're going to want in your hair arsenal. It'd almost be worth getting a new dryer just to use this, it's that good (one star off for the weirdess of the 'universal' claim.)

title: Gorgeous Korean made cushion compact plus refill.
text:
Wow! What a luxurious, well-made cushion compact. This rivals the high-end one I purchased from Lancome a few months ago. The product came boxed with the ingredients listed. The foundation I got (#2) works well with my NC20-25 skin. It's not a heavy foundation. I would consider it moderate coverage at best. title: ~ Very Nice Bentonite Clay ~ Great for Internal or External Detoxification. ~
text:
On receipt of this Aspen Naturals Bentonite Clay Amazing Skin and Body Detoxifier, there was a tamper-proof seal in place over the opening of the jar for peace of mind in knowing it arrived to me pure and untampered with. The Bentonite Clay is a fine powder is easy to use with easy-to-follow directions right on the back of the label, although there are many other uses as well. I appreciate that this came well-protected for a safe delivery, which is a big part of a product, to be able to order it and know it will arrive safe and sound.

I have used this several times as a face mask mixed with Rose Hydrosol and a drop of Frankincense Essential Oil, which worked perfectly for me. I just rubbed it gently on my face in gentle circular motions and then allowed it to try for about 15 to 20 minutes (until completely dry), and rinsed it off with a warm, wet washcloth. I do want to try it with the Apple Cider Vinegar also, since there are so many benefits to that as well. My skin is dry combination, but Bentonite Clay can be helpful for all skin types. My skin feels soft and smooth after using this as a mask and I will continue to use it one to two times per week.

I have also used this Bentonite Clay stuffed into empty capsules I purchased at Amazon to help with a tummy ache and it was a huge help with that as well. I like to keep a baggy of these capsules on hand and take four to six of them (00 size) for possible bad food ingestion. This Aspen Naturals Bentonite Clay is premium, high quality 100% Sodium Bentonite Clay powder with no fillers, binders, additives or preservatives and is wonderfully detoxifying inside and out. This makes an excellent exfoliating, skin-softening, and detoxifying facial mask AND can help when taken internally with tummy trouble, such as a flu or food poisoning. I would definitely purchase this again and can recommend it wholeheartedly. Good stuff!

title: You can pretty much use it for everything
text:
**I received this product for free in exchange for an honest and unbiased review.**

If you are looking for a good quality fractionated coconut oil, look no further, this bottle by Sky Organics is great! It has all the great qualities that fractionated coconut oil has and it is truly a multi-purpose oil. A few days ago, my face got some allergic reactions to something, everything I used and ate was normal but somehow my face got redness all over, bumpy, and it stinks when I applied my normal face product, even Argan oil. Didn't know what to do so I called up my facial lady and she said use coconut oil. So fortunate to have this bottle of fractionated coconut oil handy so I began applying it on my face. I was skeptical at first, didn't know how my skin gonna react. I have to say, it worked wonder. First, it didn't stink my skin, so I figured it was a good sign. I thought it was going to be greasy but it actually was not greasy at all. And it absorbs very quickly too, I only used like half a pump the first time, and then I reapply about 15 minutes later. I have continued applying both days and nights up until today and my skin had calmed down and it feels great. Very moisturizing, I have to say, I like it better than argan oil. Argan oil is more rich compared to fractionated coconut oil so maybe it doesnt' work as well on sensitive or inflamed skin.

If you google fractionated coconut oil, there's a looooong list of ways you can use it for. Many Do It Yourself projects, make up remover, skin moisturizer, massage oil, crayon remover, hair conditioner, helps to fade stretch marks, shaving lotion, etc, etc, etc...

I would totally recommend this bottle of fractionated coconut oil by Sky Organics, 5 stars product!

Ingredients
100% PURE MEDIUM CHAIN TRIGLYCERIDE OIL (FRACTIONATED COCONUT OIL ,COCOS NUCIFERA) COLD-PRESSED BY EXPELLER METHOD.

title: enjoying this - great in tandem with a thick skin cream
text:
My mother asked me to find her a moisturizer with matrixxyl and peptides. Very specific and she didnt want anything that did not have at least those two ingredients.

The reason is a conversation with her dermatologist. Matrixxyl is made of 2 peptides, palmitoyl-tripeptide and palmitoyl-oligopeptide, which stimulate collagen and elastin production in the skin. And peptides form a long chain of amino acids to become proteins, penetrating the top layer of skin cells and signaling the cells including collagen.

The Cazbe serum works really nicely in tandem with my moms Ponds cream (she has used Ponds as long as I remember). The serum absorbs pretty rapidly and unlike other serums, doesnt seem to leave her skin feeling sort of tight or dry. After a few minutes (she will put the serum on before brushing her teeth, and then follow with moisturizer after teeth), she will apply the Ponds cream to completely moisturize her face. Ive tried this a few times and find I can only really use it around my eyes it dries out my cheeks and chin. If used just around my eyes, it feels a lot better.

Her skin is looking beautiful. I think in combination with a really solid cream to sort of seal in the benefits, after washing your face, and just before bed, its a great part of your beauty routine.

* we received the serum for evaluation and review

title: light, floral lavender
text:
Lavender is my #1 go-to essential oil. I think I use it in 90% of my blends, whether in the diffuser or in topical blends (or sprays, etc). The only thing I definitely dont use it for is my home-made cleaning products where citrus oils are the only essential oils.

This particular oil is a very delicate scent some lavender oils can pack quite a punch in terms of the scent. This is certainly floral and has a high note to it. You can easily pick it out of a blend. Its my first oil from New York Biology and Im very pleased.

I love blending lavender in particular with chamomile, as it has an almost instantaneous calming effect. Also love to blend it with bergamot, ylang ylang, mandarin, and a drop of lime.

The bottle is very large, a dark brown color to protect the oil from UV rays which can damage the oils and decrease the shelf life. My favorite way to dispense oils is with the eye dropper (the euro droppers found in smaller bottles tend to gush several drops at once, so thats definitely not my preference) you can really control how many drops you dispense with these eye droppers.

Arrived well protected in bubble wrap and there was no leaks.

title: Great fractionated coconut oil
text:
I ordered this bottle of Fractionated Coconut Oil by Sky Organics 16oz- 100% Pure MCT Oil (Cocos Nucifera) with PUMP. Ideal as a Massage Oil & Aromatherapy. Carrier Oil Made in USA because I always keep coconut oil in my supplies for all of my diy skin care projects. This fractionated coconut oil came quickly and undamaged. It was wrapped in a plastic bag and had both a flip top pour top and a pump. This fractionated coconut oil is light and non-greasy and perfect for many of my diy projects. There is no odor so it doesn't interfere with your essential oils. This 16oz bottle will go a long way and since it is fractionated it will have a longer shelf life so don't worry if you don't use it all at once. Keeping this bottle in a cool, dry and shaded/dark place to help extend it even further by preventing light damage.
Fractionated Coconut Oil is an all-natural carrier oil that readily absorbs into the skin, making it an ideal oil for topical delivery. provides a soothing barrier without clogging pores and is excellent for dry skin and hair. It leaves skin feeling silky smooth and non-greasy,Use it to fade stretch marks, to help repair the skin, on cracked lips, discolouration patches, and even to remove makeup. If you have dry, damaged hair, its also worth trying coconut oil.The capric and caprylic acids work as antioxidants and disinfectants, and the low molecular weight of the oil means it can easily penetrate the hair shaft. Apply the coconut oil directly on to the hair and leave for 15 to 30 minutes. (do not leave it on overnight or throughout the day because it will start smelling nasty as the day progresses) Coconut oil can be used as a great natural shaving lotion. It creates a wonderfully smooth surface for razors, while nourishing and soothing the skin. Put a few drops in the palm of your hand and apply to the skin before shaving. Fractionated coconut oil has antibacterial properties and can be mixed with anti-bacterial essential oils such as cinnamon leaf, cedar atlas, ravensara, eucalyptus, bergamot, geranium, tea tree, thyme to create a natural treatment for wounds.

I am disabled and I always leave a review on products I purchase/receive. Whether good or bad, I am always honest. It makes me feel like I am productive again. And I would hate for someone to purchase something bad and waste money if I didn't say something.

title: ~ Generous 16-Ounce Bottle from a Brand I Trust! ~
text:
On receipt of this 100% Pure and Natural Fractionated Coconut Oil (Cocos Nucifera) from Sky Organics, it arrived in a plastic bag to protect any other items in my box from possible leakage. It came with a push-top dispenser in place, under which there was a rubber stopper to keep the oil from leaking on its journey to me. Also in the bag was a pump dispenser, should I prefer that. Its nice to have the choice of dispensing and the pump dispenser is my choice. It makes it so easy to fill up a little roller bottle or squeeze bottle for my concoctions AND easy to dispense when I use it as an after-shower moisturizer. The label contains all of the pertinent information, such as company contact information, product information, directions and possible uses, ingredients (100% pure medium chain triglyceride oil aka fractionated coconut oil (cocos nucifera), cold-pressed by expelier method), seals earned. I like that this is 100% pure and natural and is odorless and colorless, making it a perfect carrier oil for aromatherapy blends. This Fractionated Coconut Oil is chemical- and additive-free, non-greasy, and eco-friendly.

I use this Coconut Oil most of all in my roller ball bottle blends that I make for others and for myself more than any other use, but I also use it as an after-bath moisturizer, either by itself or mixed with my choice of essential oils. I pat it all over while my skin is still slightly damp, allowing it to sink in and keep the moisture in. I like that it is completely scent-free, so any essential oils I may add to my blends doesnt need to try to overpower the carrier oil. This is a lovely big bottle and I love the pump dispenser for use one-handed and for ease in filling bottles to just the right height. This oil also has, on its own before even adding essential oils, antifungal, antiviral and antibacterial properties. It makes a lovely massage oil and can blend with other oils for a more rounded benefit. I use this almost every day, which makes this generous 16-ounce size perfect for me. Sky Organics is one of my favorite brands and I will definitely be purchasing this again, although this bottle should last me quite some time.

title: One of My go-to Sheet Masks - Really Helps Calm Skin and Boost Hydration
text:
I'm pretty bias when it comes to the Dr. Jart+ Pore Minimalist Mask (or the Dr. Jart+ Clean Up Your Pores Mask if you are purchasing outside of the States). Both masks have the same ingredients, just different packaging. This mask is not only a go-to for me, but it's one of those masks that consistently helps with my breakouts.

A Fast Intro to One of my Favorite Masks:
Mask is black and one piece.
The scent is amazing, clean and reminds me a little of baby powder, but not overwhelming.
Mask was really easy to unfold and apply. It comes out of the package dripping with essence.
The packaging is plain, but looks clean and is easy to open.
I generally apply this mask and leave it on for 30-45 minutes.
Ingredients include charcoal, spearmint extract, and arginine. All address acne, clogged and enlarged pores.
I have a huge forehead and this mask afters great coverage. My only complaint is with the bottom half of the mask. The fit on my chin area is a little off. Anytime I start to breakout, I reach for this mask. My skin always looks so much calmer after and it boosts the hydration in my skin just a bit without making my face oily. The next morning, my skin looks healthier, acne/clogged pores look less aggravated and a lot less noticeable.

title: Thrilled with this mask!!
text:
I love this product! It comes in a small container so I was kind of bummed at first, but what little product is in here packs a powerful punch. I highly recommend this if you're looking for a clay or mud type of mask to clarify and clear your skin. I suffer from deep cystic acne and broke out earlier this week. I put on this mud mask and I could not believe how great the results were. Within one day my pimples had disappeared and even my damage spots seem to be less noticeable. My skin felt super soft and clear.

I have a pretty sensitive skin but I didn't have any irritation from this whatsoever. The package says to leave the mask on for 10 or 15 to 20 minutes but I noticed that even after 20 minutes, the mask still was not dried so I did leave it on for longer. It is a bit of a drying mask so if you already have dry skin, you will want to use a moisturizer following the mask. I found that when I combined it with my acne medication that contains benzoyl peroxide and salicylic acid, it was just to drying for my skin. Therefore, I would recommend maybe skipping a day of other chemical products when you use this mask.

The mask it goes on really nice and smooth. I used a Q-tip to mix up the mask material as the directions say to stir it each time you're going to use it. Then I just used the Q-tip to apply the mask and I from layer on my face. The mask has a cooling a fact and isn't a dry or itchy at all. It was a very pleasant experience overall. It wasn't messy at all to use either.

I posted some pictures below of the material in the jar as well as when it was on my face. That way, you can see how quickly I put the mask on my face. I hope the photos are helpful.

Again, I recognize that this is a smaller container than I had previously thought, but you don't need much to cover your entire face. Although I can't say for sure, I am guessing that I would get at least 10 to 15 masks with this product. That is quite a bit considering how much is charged for mud mask facials at spas. Do you make sure that you see all the container tightly and store it in a cool or dark place as it will dry out quickly if you leave it open.

title: Excellent formula for neck, forehead, and eyes!
text:
I love the cooling feeling from this thick gel. It has a unique push down applicator that you can simply swipe off the amount you dispense to put it on your forehead, under your chin, around your neck or around your eyes. As it dries and sinks into your skin, it makes it feel a bit tighter.

I find that the results last, for me, about 3-4 hours. This is not an issue, but I feel worth noting. This isn't an all day formula.
This formula has Hyaluronic Acid and vitamin E oil in it. Although the list of ingredients is lengthy, what I base my decision on is: does this work?
This does. The puffiness under my eyes, the crepe-y neck, the small lines on my forehead have all benefited from this gel.

title: I really can't say enough good things about this machine!
text:
*UPDATE* April 18th, 2017 - I was just browsing the net trying to find a light therapy device and I was getting pretty exasperated with too many choices. I happened to look over and see my Dermabraze MD unit on my vanity and thought, I wonder if their company makes other products? So when I Google'd the company one of the first things I saw was a "Fakespot" link, and having only ever seen products with an F rating I thought I'd check this one because I expected it to have rave reviews like mine. I was FLOORED when I saw the grade F! That simply cannot be accurate! I purchased mine in November of 2016, and nearly 6 months later I still regard it as the best money I've ever spent on skincare, PERIOD. I used it on my full face just last night! It gets a regular workout too, between myself, my mother and my daughter. Even my son has used it! I just had to come update my review when I saw that deceitful grade but in a way I'm thankful because I know now that Fakespot can't be trusted. I KNOW THIS DEVICE WORKS AND WORKS FANTASTICALLY!

I'm fortunate to have had a great example when I was a child. My mother always took very good care of her skin. Until I reached my teen years I literally believed that all women used peel off masks, apricot scrub, Noxema and Oil of Olay, lol. Skin care has come a long way, and when I started working in the beauty industry I was introduced to higher quality products and left my mother's favorites in the dust, haha. As far as exfoliating, before trying this machine I'd always stuck with scrubs, chemical exfoliants and microdermabrasion crystal creams. Now I feel like a need a good kick in the rear for not investing in real microdermabrasion years ago! I absolutely love this machine ... it is an investment, but the effectiveness and sheer convenience of it make it more than worth the money. You just can't get results like this with any other method. My favorite thing about it is the suction. Sure, you can use products to manually exfoliate skin, but vacuuming the oil and dead cells that collect inside and clog pores combined with abrasion literally and immediately take years off the skin's appearance. It also allows the high dollar serums and moisturizers we apply to do a much better job. Again, to me this totally justifies the investment. If you're serious about skin care and spend good money on expensive products, you owe it to yourself to prep your skin so your products can do their jobs!

Pros of the Bright Therapy unit:

Rechargeable
Strong, adjustable suction
Different attachments for heavy, light and acute abrasion.
Comfortable to hold, fit's easily in the hand
Has disposable filters allowing you to see exactly what the machine removes every time you use it.

If you're looking for a great quality microdermabrasion system I think you'll be pleased with this one, I can't find a single con to owning it. I absolutely love mine!

title: Undecided still.
text:
This is perhaps one of the most difficult reviews that I have written in a while. Usually I know immediately if the product is a hit or miss, but Vitabrid C12 is different. I cant decide. Im torn. After using VC12 for about 3 weeks, I am still unsure of the results.

The concept: Vitamin C is slow released thru the skin by mixing a small amount of VC12, with water or a moisturizer, onto the face and neck. The results, brighter, smoother and firmer skin. The powder comes in a convenient small bottle (about the length of your thumb) with a small spoon (used for measuring). Simply mix the appropriate amount - I use about 2 spoonfuls since I put it on my face and neck- with a lightweight moisturizer. I didnt notice any tightness, irritation or itching after I applied this to my skin (i.e., face and neck). I simply apply my makeup as usual. With that being said, I havent noticed anything bad either -no additional breakouts and no nasty white film (left on my face from bad blending). But I also havent looked in the mirror and said wow or gosh, this is like a facelift in a bottle moment. Not to mention that this product takes a little more effort than my usual skincare regime. I am not use to mixing products before I use them. **Therefore, I am going to give this product 3 stars BUT continue to use it for a little longer to see if I am wowed. After all each container is believed to last about 3 months. If I notice something earth shattering in the next month or so, I will amend my review. Otherwise, this review will stand.

title: Nice look; feels pretty solid; but average in performance & value
text:
This is a dressed up version of the Wahl LifeProof shaver (which I also reviewed). It has a more upscale look and feel to it, plus adds a battery gauge to show the charge level. However, the shave quality is the same OK, but not a standout.

The case feels more solid than the LifeProof and, while its more of a traditional look, I think they did a nice job with the overall aesthetics. It is pretty grippy even with wet hands. It does not, however, feel as comfortable to hold as the more sculpted models such as most of the Panasonic shavers and some Braun shavers.

The shave quality of this model is identical to that of the LifeProof: very Remington in how it feels (close, but rather aggressive). Performance is best on the easy spots (cheek) but not as good on the more trickier spots (neck and jawline). The flex head helps with dealing with face contours but it lacks enough travel to do an excellent quality job.

The aggressiveness of the shave is dialed down when using it wet. It needs a very, very thin layer of shave cream (the gel style creams work well) or the head gets bogged down.

Love the trimmer! The positioning could be improved to make it easier to use, but it cuts very cleanly on sideburns and shash trimming.

The controls are clean, easy to read and tell you all you need to know (charge and battery status).

I like the feel of this better than the Wahl LifeProof, but the shave quality keeps this at the same rating (average, which is 3 stars). Its a very workable shaver, but for the price there are better choices available from Panasonic (anything in their Arc line) or, for less money, from Remington.

title: Lightens Your Face But Kind of Overpriced For What You Get
text: This is a small bottle of powder that comes with a tiny spoon.  You dab a bit of the white powder into your hand and mix it with your regular moisturizer, which you then apply to your face. I used a little water and my usual Aveeno moisturizer with SPF 15 sunblock.  My face does look a little brighter after using it for a week but the effect is somewhat similar to using a light-colored makeup foundation.  Unfortunately it has little effect on my crow's-feet or my small "laugh lines". It's OK but since I can get the same effect applying certain types of makeup or concealers, it's chief benefit is that it's good to use when you don't want to wear makeup and want something that has a lighter feel on your face. Otherwise, the price is kind of high for what you get.

title: Absolutely the BEST for nail art and I've tried MANY!
text:
Good liquid latex is every nail artist's best friend. I decided to purchase this jar after using up my supply of prepared/bottled liquid latex varieties, and I am so glad I did. Prior to discovering Liquid Latex Fashions, I was buying liquid latex marketed as "nail art tape". In terms of package price and the consistent quality of product, I find that this is the much better option. As long as I continue to stamp, water marble and do gradient nails I will continue to use THIS. Here are the highlights as to why I think Liquid Latex Fashions is superior to all the rest:

* Package size is 4 ounces and an ample supply for simple nail art. It is smaller in real life than what it appears in the ad photos. I have been using this as my go-to for the past six months and have barely made a dent in it. I suspect that it will probably dry up before I can get through it all.
* Product is simple to decant - the large mouth on the jar makes it easy to use an infant medicine syringe to draw the liquid up and dispense into a clean nail polish bottle. (You can get the plastic medi syringes for free at the pharmacy counter - all you have to do is ask.)
* Consistency is thin/watery, which is easy to apply and dries very fast. It turns to a dark pink when it's dry. One layer works great for me, but you can add more layers if needed.
* It peels so good! Always a clean peel in one solid sheet - no bits and pieces of latex that break off. You can literally roll your fingertip across the edge and peel it off in one whole piece. No more fighting with latex removal after doing a gorgeous gradient!
* FYI: Ammonia free does not mean odorless. This product does not smell good at all. If you've used any type of liquid latex before, you know it does have a distinguishable smell. It is somewhere between fish oil and cat urine. Or a mixture of both. Yeah, it stinks to be perfectly honest. Just be forewarned.
* Pricing of this is so much more economical versus prepared varieties. In fact, I wouldn't be surprised if some folks weren't just repackaging this and slapping their brand labels on it.
* The bonus to THIS particular liquid latex - it's black light reactive... so if you plan on going to an all-night rave anytime soon, you can wear this and you'll glow all night! lol ;)


Highly recommended and I will most definitely repurchase when I hit tub bottom. Thanks for reading!

Seriously though, one more thing - In order to keep the latex fresh and from drying up, you should make sure to wipe any excess latex from around the neck of the jar. Keep the lid screwed on tight when not in use, and store it in a cool dry place.

title: Great quality and selection...
text:
I'm so happy I bought this eyeliner set. The colors are extremely vivid, and they pop, even on my darker skin. I'm a black eyeliner fanatic, and have been wanting to switch things up. I love the mix of colors, which includes average, everyday colors as well as colors appropriate for a night out. They aren't clumpy or runny, and they stay put nicely.

The formula was a pleasant surprise. These pencils glide smoothly, even over eyeshadow and my waterline. The waterline is always a challenging area, because I tear up easily and often. I can create a sharp line or smudge it out, and either way, it wears extremely well. In one photo, I'm wearing black on the waterline and inner corner, and in the other, I'm wearing champagne on the waterline.

I like that these liners each arrive sealed, but be aware that the plastic can be tough to get off, and also that the liners are extremely soft. I broke one unwrapping it, but luckily, they sharpen well, without constantly breaking. The quality, value, and variety of this set are excellent, overall...it's a win.

title: Great conditioner. Keep your beard happy.
text:
When you start getting a decent beard you realize the value of beard balms and oils. After you shampoo your beard you basically strip it of oils and dirt. That is good but you have to replace the oils if you don't want the dreaded beard itch and dandruff. This stuff does a great job at replacing the striped oils. It keeps my beard happy and that helps keep me happy. I also enjoy the sent of this balm. It is a mild sent of citrus orange in my opinion. I have used others with less sent and some that are much stronger. This sent seems to leave about an hour after applying.

Pros:
Natural ingredients
Good conditioning
Easy to use tin.
Easy to apply consistency

Cons:
If I use it multiple times in day I started to get zits in certain areas.

All in all. It is a good product and keeps my beard looking and feeling good.

title: A more affordable version of Bliss' Lemon + Sage Body Butter
text:
FACT: The founder of Bliss is *also* is the founder of Soap and Glory, so it makes sense to replicate the success of Bliss' Lemon & Sage Body Butter with this *verrrry* similar-smelling body cream. Despite the name, Orangeasm doesn't smell like oranges--- it's fragranced with Bergamot and Lemon (the description states "green mandarins" for those not-in-the-know, to indicate that it's not a juicy or sweet scent -- but more rindy and zesty type. Refreshing and energizing, unisex, and a near-scent-twin for Lemon & Sage. The texture smooths and absorbs just like Bliss', and rapidly soaks in to hydrate without leaving any greasy trace. A definitively more reasonably-priced version of a bodycare classic.

Ingredients: Aqua (Water), Glycerin, Butyrospermum parkii (Shea) butter, Cetearyl alcohol, Glyceryl stearate, PEG-100 stearate, Vitis vinifera (Grape) seed oil, Prunus amygdalus dulcis (Sweet almond) oil, Mangifera indica (mango) seed butter, Theobroma cacao (Cocoa) seed butter, Dimethicone, Olea europaea (Olive) fruit oil, Phenoxyethanol, Dipropylene glycol, Limonene, Parfum (Fragrance), Caprylyl glycol, Sodium polyacrylate, Carbomer, PPG-20 methyl glucose ether, Citrus limon (Lemon) peel oil, Ethylhexylglycerin, Menthyl lactate,Xanthan gum, Tocopheryl acetate, Mica, Potassium hydroxide, BHT, Butylene glycol, Panax ginseng root extract, Citrus reticulata (Tangerine) peel oil, Linalool, Camellia oleifera leaf extract, Citral, Tetrasodium EDTA, Pogostemon cablin oil, Alpha-isomethyl ionone, Citrus aurantium amara (Bitter Orange) leaf/twig oil, Glyceryl acrylate/acrylic acid copolymer,Citrus aurantium dulcis peel extract, Schinus terebinthifolius seed extract, Polyester-3, Gelatin, Acacia senegal gum, Citrus aurantium dulcis (Orange) peel oil, Pelargonium graveolens flower oil, Gynostemma pentaphyllum leaf extract, Benzoic acid, Sodium benzoate, Potassium sorbate, Denatonium benzoate, Dehydroacetic acid, Lavandula angustifolia (Lavender) oil, CI 77891 (Titanium dioxide), CI 19140 (Yellow 5), CI 45370 (Orange 5), CI 16035 (Red 40).

text:

Overall I think I prefer using their brushes with rounded sides, and I think their shape feels more natural in the hand as well. Still, I have no complaints about this one, and I really like the texture of it. The pleasant point to this one probably renders this a tie. Basically, I think you need a Real Techniques Face Sponge, but I don't think it matters which one; since the other is cheaper, I would probably go with it.

It is a very soft sponge, pleasant feeling on the skin, and it seems made from quality material. It washes clean and dries well.

title: ~ Moisturizing, Softening, Frizz-Taming ~
text:
My hair is thick, wavy, and color-treated. This Premium Nature Argan Oil Shampoo, Conditioner, and Thermal Shield Set works well for my hair type. The Argan Oil provides the extra conditioning I need without weighing my hair down. Although the bottles are smaller than the ones they sell separately, I like that these come in a set, since they all work great together. I see that most reviewers love the scent of these. That is the only thing I don't particularly like. Although the scent is unisex, it smells a little too masculine for my preference, but that is just my own preference. I love the handy flip lids on the shampoo and conditioner and the sprayer is great for the thermal shield. A huge plus to me is when a product comes with tamper-proofing, which this set comes completely wrapped in plastic, so I know it has not been tampered with.

The shampoo is rich and opaque and, just from the creaminess, I knew this would work well on my hair. The clear shampoos are usually not conditioning enough (in general), but the creamy ones, like this, are great. The conditioner is the same, very thick and rich, perfect for my wavy, dry, color-treated hair. It may weigh finer hair down a bit much, unless used more sparsely. The thermal shield helps keep my waves from becoming frizzy. It is lightly conditioning and softening. It sprays evenly and just the right amount. I like these being sold in the set for trial purposes and then the ability to purchase them separate as well, once you run out or the smaller set sizes.

This is a nice set of wonderfully moisturizing, softening, and frizz-taming products that add shine, bounce, and softness.

title: Works surprisingly well
text:
I've seen these steamer machines that are used to remove gel nail polish and while I've always wanted to try them, I was very skeptical and unwilling to spend the money on a gadget that may or may not work. But, removing the gel polish is the worst part or the thing I hate about gel polish: it's time consuming and so hard on the nail bed. I've seen mixed reviews online about gel polish steamers but I finally decided to try one.
This gel polish remover machine actually works. It was easy to put together and I was able to completely remove my gel polish in under 20 minutes. First and most important is to file the top layer of gel down first with a nail file before using this device. I was not able to get the gel polish offf without filing the surface first. I put about two capfuls of 100% acetone (you can use less) into the little tray and turned the machine on. Once it beeps, you can stick your fingers inside. It gets a little hot but it's not painful. After five minutes the machine will beep and I am able to scrape off most of the gel polish. I have to do a second round to get certain areas that just won't scrape off. And when I say scrape off, I mean easily scrape off not scraping and hurting the surface of the nail. I guess I should say push off the gel polish to remove it. I leave the remaining acetone in the tray and either reuse it or dump it. I would say this is easier than using aluminum foil or plastic nail caps because you do the whole hand at once. With foil or plastic caps, I never get my whole hand done at once. This was easier and I didn't use any cotton balls and I used less acetone.

The device is a little pricey. It's basically a warming plate fitted inside a contained area with holes to place your fingers. It's worth the money to me because I hate the process of gel removal. I like that the company provides four replacement plastic pieces for the nail holes. It took me a while to figure out what the replacement pieces were for but after reading one of the reviews I now realize what it's used for. There is also a second plastic tray to put the nail polish remover or acetone in. My only criticism is that I wish the device was smaller as I have a lot of nail stuff and this will just add to it all. It's not the fanciest looking device but it does the job.

title: Oz Naturals makes great products.
text:
Oz Naturals is a favorite go-to of mine for beauty products. I have tried many of their moisturizers, serums, and facial cleansers and am never disappointed.

This is a one ounce glass bottle, pump action. Clear serum.

Though I can't know what it does on a cellular level, really, I do know that using Oz products (along with other good skin care products and eating healthfully, along with exercise and good sleep, and genes - really, the stuff we put on our faces is only a part of good skin care) keeps my skin looking good. Many people can't tell my age, and that means I'm doing something right. So since Oz Naturals is also reasonably priced (under $18 at time of this reveiw), I feel good about purchasing it.

What I wish is that it were easier to pump - it kind of jets out so it's more difficult to control how much you want.

This is not a "luxe feel" type of serum, so be aware of that. It feels more dry (though not drying to your skin-there's just no sits-on-top-of-skin thicker feel that some serums have) after you put it on rather than with that emollient feeling some serums have. That's probably also because of the hydraulic acid quality in it. It's a serum blend of hydraulic acid, vitamin E, retinol, and other ingredients.

I use this at night, applying it to my cleansed face. I wait a few minutes and then I apply my moisturizer.

Love their product; love their company.

title: Okay but nothing special.
text:
A plastic jar full of lavender-colored and -scented bath salts. (Apparently some of my Pre De Provence products are showing up in one review - so while this reveiw is for bath salts, I have the lavender lotion as well, which I do love the scent of it but as with the bath salts, wish the bottle were nicer).

There was no seal on the top of the jar, just the lid. That's fine, but I would wonder how long it would sit on a shelf before purchasing and how "fresh" the scent would last. That said, when I opened the lid and took a whiff, it was pretty powerfully scented. I like the lavender aspect but there's another scent there that I don't like and can't figure out what it is. It's off-putting. It doesn't linger in the water, so that's good.

I sprinkled some in my bathroom sink that I'd filled with warm water. The water turned a slight lavender shade as the bath salts turned clear. The salt crystals did melt pretty quickly, though as with any bath salts I've used there are always a few that are stubborn.

The water felt soft enough, I suppose-nothing really special, but that strong scent wasn't as apparent in the diluted water.

I did think it a bit pricey at just under $17 (at time of this review). For that price, I'd like a glass bottle or something prettier in the jar design itself, though the lavender-colored crystals do look pretty. Still, there are plenty of bath salts out there that are half the price and smell about the same, so what would make me want to purchase this one exclusively? Something that made it attractive to me, and that would be a pretty bottle/jar that I could display in my bathroom in my basket of bath goodies. Or, to give someone as a gift.

This plastic jar makes it seem like one of those cheaper jars of bath salts you can buy at Big Lots, which I can do for less than half the price if I want bath salts. Pretty it up some so I feel I'm getting my money's worth. You cold say Pre De Provence has quality ingredients and maybe that's why the price, but I'm not finding it special enough to pay almost $17.

title: Bamboo pin brush, comb, fluff brush.  SEE PIX
text:
I have 2 standard poodles and their hair needs daily attention. As their hair texture is very tightly curled and soft, it tends to mat easily.
I love these brushes for raking their hair and then fluffing it up.
The comb has rotating pins so that it will glide through their tangles easily and not pull.
As anyone who has brushed a tangled cat or dog, you know that any discomfort that they feel will likely mean that you will get some teeth marks on your hand and the dreaded 'smile' with all their teeth showing.
This set comes in a pretty canvas drawstring bag and has solid bamboo handles. The grips on the handles have raised silicone pads to keep your hand from getting fatigued...and to prevent them from slipping when Pooch or Kitty decides to grab it and run off.
I'm happy with this set. You get all 3 grooming tools in the set: pin brush, fluff brush, pin comb.
Makes my dogs happy and keeps their hair looking awesome...till they roll on the grass :)

title: This is the greatest invention I've stumbled upon
text:
Even with various gloves and pads, washing makeup brushes is always a pain. You always get your hands wet and prune-y.

This is the greatest invention I've stumbled upon. It's very easy to choose a boot, insert your brush, and spin wash. I used this to clean ALL of my makeup brushes and it worked well for almost every single one. Each brush needs to be positioned a little differently for optimal cleaning depending on the shape and length of fibers. The only brushes that didn't work well were bulky face brushes with heavy handles that the machine did not spin well and small eyeshadow and detailing brushes that couldn't fan out. I recommend two rounds of rinsing. The first in soapy bubbly water to clean the brushes and the second in clean water only to rinse out any bubbles and residue.

Even with two cycles, the process was quicker and less intensive than washing by hand and the drying time was cut down to almost nothing for nearly all my brushes, including dense synthetics.

I highly recommend!

text: I'm really on a kick of trying the whole OZ line...and I am in love with all of it. In fact, I find a way to use every serum over two days. I use Retin A every other night and use the vitamin c serum after using it. The next night, I use the Vitamin c with AHA and the Hyaluronic acid serums along with this one. I do wait about 10-15 minuites between each. But, I use the eye gel every night. They all work so well together and my skin is looking and feeling so much better. My biggest problems are large pores and uneven texture. My texture has evened out so much and my pores are surprising me more each day. I'd say these serums really have made the biggest difference in my pores. I kept seeing my grandmother's nose in the mirror, and I'm only 46--I was really self conscious.
